Tech rout drags China shares lower after SEC hints at delistings1. Hong Kong-listed tech giants dragged Chinese stocks lower on Friday after the U.S. Securities Exchange Commission (SEC) identified Chinese companies that will be delisted if they do not provide access to audit documents.2. The Hang Seng Tech Index (.HSTECH) dived more than 7%  dragging the Hang Seng Index (.HSI) down more than 3%  while China's onshore CSI300 Index (.CSI300) dropped more than 1% in early trade.3. Companies on the SEC list that are also listed in Hong Kong led the slump on Friday. Yum China Holdings (9987.HK)  Zai Lab   HUTCHMED (China) Ltd (0013.HK) and Beigene Ltd (6160.HK) fell between 8% and 15%.More here
